Once the installation is successful and all basic configurations are completed, the Doxee Workplace can be integrated into MS Dynamics anywhere. This is done in Power Apps – [https://make.powerapps.com](https://make.powerapps.com)

**Note**: This must be integrated into the "Main" Dataverse, so please check which environment you are in:

## 4.1. Integration 
Under Tables, select the desired object (e.g., Contact). Choose Forms under Data Experiences.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Then select the form where the object should be inserted – for example, in the main form.

The component can now be embedded in any text field. To do this, select a text field (where the Doxee Workplace should be displayed), open the Component tab on the left side, and click the plus sign to add a new one.

**Example**: 

Click on the Component and chose 1-column tab. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on the New Tab to edit the tab. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

On the right side you can now edit the tab. Under Label you can choose the name that will appear also in CRM for this tab. By clicking on the section below you will activate the edit menu for the content of your new app. The Label represents the content title. 

![A white screen with a white border  Description automatically generated with medium confidence](data:image/png;base64,)

Now you need to add a text component to the content section. Try to search for “text” in the Components Search on the left side. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)  

Drag and drop the text editor to the content section. In the Table column you need to select one of the text fields. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on the newly added element and expand Components in the edit menu on the right side of the window. Click on the Component. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

If the Infinica component is not part of the menu, click on Get more components. You will find InfinicaWorkplace under Built by others tab. Chose the InfinicaWorkplace from the Add component menu.

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

In the Configuration Reference you need to add the reference from Iframe Configurations. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)

Click on Save and publish in the right top corner. 

![A screenshot of a computer  Description automatically generated](data:image/png;base64,)
